chunk_content: Patients that restart treatment after 4 150 weeks or more of being off ARVs should also be counted under TX_RTT in the reporting period in which the patient returns to care and restarts ARVs. T TX_CURR should be reported from both PEPFAR-supported sites in the private and/or public sector. R E Patients currently receiving treatment from mobile clinics can be reported in two ways. Firstly, if the A mobile clinic is associated with (e.g., receives commodities, reports to, is staffed by) a nearby health T facility, then these individuals should be reported by that facility. Secondly, if a mobile clinic is M stationary for more than 2 reporting periods, it should be added to the PEPFAR facility list with E N geocodes and data should be reported for this mobile clinic directly. T DO NOT include: Patients who receive ARVs for post-exposure prophylaxis (PEP) or short-term ART only for prevention (PrEP) should not be reported in this indicator.
